cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper proposes a method for pruning deep neural networks, specifically convolutional neural networks, to reduce their storage and computation cost. This topic is closely related to machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper focuses on neuron level pruning, which is a common technique in neural network compression (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the effectiveness of the proposed method on image classification tasks, which is a common application of convolutional neural networks in natural language processing (cs.CL).
